title: Prep roundup: Wheaton Warrenville South girls golf places third at state tournament
text:
Prep roundup: Wheaton Warrenville South girls golf places third at state tournament Published: Thursday, Oct. 22, 2015 4:17 p.m. CDT By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
Wheaton Warrenville South’s girls golf team earned a third-place team trophy in Class AA with a 640 score at the state tournament Oct. 16 and 17. 
Sarah Hauenstein was the Tigers’ top scorer, finishing 16th overall with a 158 score. Emma Field and Annalee Dannegger both tied for 26th with a 161 total, and Hadley Moritz tied for 31st with a 162 score. Priya Desai (40th, 165) and Julia Hauenstein (97th, 192) also played for South. 
BOYS GOLF 
Wheaton Warrenville South 
Wheaton Warrenville South’s Sean McCaffrey shot a 157 to finish in a tie for 19th place at the Class 3A boys golf state tournament Oct. 16 and 17. 
St. Francis 
In the Class 2A tournament, St. Francis was second as a team with a 638 score. 
Jonathan Nocek led the Spartans with a 150 score that was good for a seventh-place tie individually. Luke Armbrust (18th, 154), Ryan Keefe (46th, 166), Connor Reinke (68th, 171), Connor Buckley (81st, 173) and Kevin Doherty (103rd, 182) also played at state for St. Francis. 
Wheaton Academy 
Wheaton Academy’s Grant Gosden placed 68th overall with a 171 score in Class 2A. 
GIRLS TENNIS 
Wheaton Warrenville South 
Samantha Choi was second in singles and Katya Shcherbyna fourth in singles as both moved on from the Oct. 17 Naperville North sectional to the state tournament, which begins Oct. 22. 
Wheaton North 
Madeline Fidel placed third in singles at the Naperville North sectional Oct. 17 to move on to the state tournament. 
Wheaton Academy 
Maisie Howard and Lily Bracy were third in doubles Oct. 17 at the Naperville North sectional to move on to the state tournament. 
GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY 
Wheaton North 
Rose Quinn (20th, 18:18) paced the Falcons at the DuPage Valley Conference meet Oct. 17. 
Kailee Sowers, Bridget Berry, Jill Humecke and Kiersten Oslund were also scoring runners for the Falcons, who placed sixth as a team. 
Wheaton Warrenville South 
Sara Atkins (second, 17:05) and Allison McGrath (seventh, 17:28) led the Tigers to second place at the DuPage Valley Conference meet Oct. 17. 
Emma Schroer, Mary Erdman and Kendall Laveen also contributed to South’s team score of 80 points. 
BOYS CROSS COUNTRY 
Wheaton North 
Matthew Beckerman (10th, 15:19) led the way for North at the DuPage Valley Conference meet Oct. 17. 
Justin Ostrem, Jordan Hennings, Alex Frank and T.J. Watson were also part of the scoring quintet as North placed second as a team with 92 points. 
Wheaton Warrenville South 
Kyle Thompson (27th, 15:50) was the top finisher for the Tigers at the DVC meet. Matthew Moore, Joseph Kratz, John Franke and Anthony Cipriano were also scoring runners as South placed seventh with 160 points.
